Observation Details: Audio has  chip and flight calls of both BTGW and NOPA. Both were side by side foraging in bush. I have used the same audio for NOPA. I have listed the different calls under the audio file comments.

Background Species: Vireo olivaceus -- Red-eyed Vireo; Dryobates pubescens -- Downy Woodpecker
Observation Details: Recorded a never before heard call from this species. The bird did eventually start making a typical Zee Zee Zee Zoo Zee but this was a short buzzy sometime two note call I have not heard before. The recording captured these calls.
